    <para styleclass="Normal"><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true">Okay, so you were humbled when the newsagent informed you that your first &quot;lottery winning&quot; program didn&apos;t always generate valid tickets. Some of the numbers were duplicated! However, if you select all of the lines in the above, somewhat more complex, expression and use </text><text styleclass="Normal" style="font-style:italic;" translate="true">Display It</text><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true">, you should now get a valid ticket.</text></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"><text styleclass="Normal" style="font-size:9pt;" translate="true">This experiment uses the, rather useful, Smalltalk </text><text styleclass="Normal" style="font-size:9pt; font-style:italic;" translate="true">Set</text><text styleclass="Normal" style="font-size:9pt;" translate="true"> collection class to avoid getting duplicates. We just have to write a loop that goes around &#160;adding the random ticket numbers to a set until we get six unique values</text><text styleclass="Normal" style="font-size:8pt;" translate="true">.</text></para>
